cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DM. 

The problem of string reconstruction from substrings is a fundamental problem in computer science and has applications in DNA sequencing. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also deals with information theory and randomness, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves analyzing algorithms and their performance, which could place it under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
